HEADWORD: Diageotropism
<hw>Di`a*ge*ot"ro*pism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The tendency of organs (as roots) of plants to
assume a position oblique or transverse to a direction towards the
center of the earth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diaglyph</ent>⟦br⟧
